import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['size'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between size and parent?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    parent_count = data['parent'].value_counts()
    parent_count = parent_count[:10,]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
    sns.barplot(parent_count.index, parent_count.values, alpha=0.8)
    plt.title('What are the most common parent values?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Number of Occurrences', fontsize=12)
    plt.xlabel('Parent', fontsize=12)
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
